theorem interior_diff_eq_diff_of_open
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hB : IsOpen (B : Set X)) :
    interior ((A \ B) : Set X) = interior A \ closure (B : Set X) := by
  classical
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `⊆` direction
    intro x hx
    -- `x` lies in `interior A` since `A \ B ⊆ A`.
    have hx_intA : x ∈ interior A := by
      have hSub : (A \ B : Set X) ⊆ A := by
        intro y hy; exact hy.1
      exact (interior_mono hSub) hx
    -- Use the neighborhood supplied by `hx` to show `x ∉ closure B`.
    have hx_not_clB : x ∉ closure (B : Set X) := by
      -- Unpack the interior membership.
      rcases (mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds).1 hx with
        ⟨U, hUopen, hxU, hUsub⟩
      -- If `x ∈ closure B`, every neighborhood meets `B`, contradicting
      -- `U ⊆ A \ B`.
      intro hx_cl
      have hNon : (U ∩ B).Nonempty :=
        (mem_closure_iff.1 hx_cl) U hUopen hxU
      rcases hNon with ⟨y, hyU, hyB⟩
      have hNotB : y ∉ B := (hUsub hyU).2
      exact hNotB hyB
    exact And.intro hx_intA hx_not_clB
  · -- `⊇` direction
    intro x hx
    rcases hx with ⟨hxIntA, hx_not_clB⟩
    -- Obtain an open neighborhood of `x` contained in `A`.
    rcases (mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds).1 hxIntA with
      ⟨U, hUopen, hxU, hUsubA⟩
    -- Remove the (closed) `closure B` to avoid `B`.
    let W : Set X := U \ closure (B : Set X)
    have hWopen : IsOpen W := hUopen.diff isClosed_closure
    have hxW : x ∈ W := by
      have : x ∈ U := hxU
      have : x ∉ closure (B : Set X) := hx_not_clB
      simp [W, *]
    -- Everything in `W` lies in `A \ B`.
    have hWsub : (W : Set X) ⊆ A \ B := by
      intro y hyW
      have hyU : y ∈ U := hyW.1
      have hyNotCl : y ∉ closure (B : Set X) := hyW.2
      have hyA : y ∈ A := hUsubA hyU
      have hyNotB : y ∉ B := by
        intro hyB
        exact hyNotCl (subset_closure hyB)
      exact And.intro hyA hyNotB
    -- `x` therefore belongs to the interior of `A \ B`.
    have hxInt : x ∈ interior (A \ B) :=
      (interior_maximal hWsub hWopen) hxW
    exact hxInt

theorem interior_inter_interior_subset
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior ((A ∩ interior B) : Set X) ⊆ interior A ∩ interior B := by
  intro x hx
  -- First, show `x ∈ interior A`.
  have hA : x ∈ interior A := by
    -- `A ∩ interior B ⊆ A`
    have hSub : (A ∩ interior B : Set X) ⊆ A := by
      intro y hy
      exact hy.1
    -- Apply monotonicity of `interior`.
    exact (interior_mono hSub) hx
  -- Next, show `x ∈ interior B`.
  have hB : x ∈ interior B := by
    -- `A ∩ interior B ⊆ interior B`
    have hSub : (A ∩ interior B : Set X) ⊆ interior B := by
      intro y hy
      exact hy.2
    -- Apply monotonicity of `interior`.
    exact (interior_mono hSub) hx
  -- Combine the two inclusions.
  exact And.intro hA hB
